pageContext.claim: “We have 2000 people now under arrest that we've taken out of various cities.”
pageContext.analysis: As of Oct. 20, the federal government had arrested more than 300 people — 286 of which are defendants in federal cases — according to an AP tally. Some of those arrested do identify as part of left-wing activist groups, but others are part of right wing groups. The Department of Justice reports more than 2,000 arrests took place as part of Operation Legend, but if those defendants were charged, they were not charged in federal court and the arrests were made in conjunction with state and local law enforcement.
